What is MongoDB?
Type: A NoSQL database.
Storage: Saves data in collections (similar to tables in SQL).
Format: Data is stored as objects (like JSON).

Key Points
NoSQL: It doesn't use rows and columns.
Collections: Similar to tables but store data as objects.

Installation
Download: Get MongoDB from the official website
https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community-kubernetes-operator

Using MongoDB
GUI Method
Create Database: Name your database and collection.
Add Data:
Click "Add Data" and "Insert Document".
remove all code and creata a object like 
{
    "name":"product 1",
    "image":"1.jpg"
}
record is created 

Command Line Method
Open MONGOSH: The MongoDB shell.
Commands:
Show Databases: show databases
Use Database: use demo1
Show Collections: show collections
Create Collection: db.createCollection('categories')
Rename Collection: db.categories.renameCollection('brands')
Insert Document: db.test.insertOne({name: 'man', image: '1.jpg'})